################################################################################
# 1K Words — repo-wide ignore net (defense in depth).
# Every subproject also has its own .gitignore; these top-level rules make sure
# secrets never slip through even from a newly added folder.
################################################################################

# ── Secrets & environment ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Templates that forkers copy end in ".example" and ARE committed.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/.dev.vars
**/.dev.vars.*
!**/.dev.vars.example
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/secrets.json
# .NET user secrets / per-env appsettings (keep the base one)
**/appsettings.*.json
!**/appsettings.json

# ── Cloudflare (personal ids / local state) ───────────────────────────────
/cloudflare-server/wrangler.jsonc
/client/wrangler.toml
**/.wrangler/

# ── Dependencies, build output, generated code ────────────────────────────
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.prisma/
**/src/generated/
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# ── Local databases (dev only) ────────────────────────────────────────────
**/*.db
**/*.sqlite
**/*.sqlite3

# ── Logs, OS & editor clutter ─────────────────────────────────────────────
**/*.log
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*
**/pnpm-debug.log*
coverage/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.idea/
.vscode/*
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/settings.json
# ── System word-set content (imported via scripts/import-system-sets.mjs) ──
/systemdata/*
!/systemdata/README.md
